---
import Deck from '../layouts/Deck.astro';
import AboutStakater from '../components/slides/AboutStakater.astro';
import Partnership from '../components/slides/Partnership.astro';
---
<Deck title="Stakater | Enterprise Account Executive" persona="Enterprise Account Executive">

  <!-- 1. Hero -->
  <section>
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>
        Your OpenShift Accounts<br/>
        <span class="highlight">Have Untapped ARR.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2 style="color:#5a5668; font-weight:500; font-size:32px;">
        How Stakater converts installed accounts into expanding platforms.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Opening frame — establish the thesis in the first 20 seconds.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Thanks for the time. What I'm going to show you today is a specific ARR problem that lives inside your existing OpenShift accounts — accounts you've already closed — and a model for unlocking it. Not new logos. Existing base. Let's walk through it."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. About Stakater -->
  <AboutStakater />

  <!-- 3. Partnership -->
  <Partnership />

  <!-- 4. The Problem -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>
        Red Hat Wins the Sale.<br/>
        <span class="highlight">Accounts Stop Growing After Year One.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:32px;">

        <div style="padding:30px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:14px; font-size:22px;">Year 0</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Subscription sold.<br/>
            Implementation delivered.<br/>
            Cluster live.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:14px; font-size:22px;">Year 1</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Engagement ends.<br/>
            Adoption slows.<br/>
            Nodes flat.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:14px; font-size:22px;">Year 2+</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Renewal at risk.<br/>
            No portfolio adoption.<br/>
            No expansion conversation.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Installed <span class="highlight">≠</span> Adopted <span class="highlight">≠</span> Expanding
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Walk left to right through the timeline. Pause on Year 2+.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Here's the pattern. Year zero — deal closes, implementation happens, cluster goes live. Year one — the partner disengages, adoption slows, nobody is driving workloads onto the platform. Year two-plus — renewal arrives and the customer is asking what they actually got. Installed does not mean adopted. Adopted does not mean expanding. That's the gap. And that's where ARR is being left."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. The Lifecycle Gap -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        The <span class="highlight">Lifecycle Gap</span> Is Where ARR Lives
      </h1>
      <br/>
      <p style="text-align:center; margin:0 auto;">
        Between subscription sold and strategic adoption, there is a gap nobody owns.
      </p>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:80px; align-items:start;">

        <div style="padding:30px; background:white; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#5a5668; margin-bottom:20px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">What Red Hat Delivers</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32;">
            World-class software platform.<br/>
            Proven subscription model.<br/>
            Implementation support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:20px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">What Drives Expansion</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32;">
            Continuous operational coaching.<br/>
            Governance and Dev & Ops alignment.<br/>
            Workload onboarding acceleration.<br/>
            Portfolio introduction at the right moment.<br/>
            Multi-cluster standardization strategy.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        Stakater owns the lifecycle gap <span class="highlight">so your ARR grows.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">The left column is not a criticism — frame it as Red Hat doing what it's built to do.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Red Hat does what it's built to do — best platform in the market, strong subscription motion, solid implementation. But what drives ARR growth is what happens after: workloads accelerating, governance maturing, teams aligned on DevOps, the right portfolio conversation at the right moment. That's the lifecycle gap. Nobody in the current partner model owns it. We do. That's specifically what we were built for."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Three Commercial Levers -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        Three Levers That <span class="highlight">Grow Your Number</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:50px;">

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:28px; margin-bottom:16px;">Workload Acceleration</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            More production workloads on OpenShift.<br/>
            More nodes consumed.<br/>
            ARR grows organically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:28px; margin-bottom:16px;">Portfolio Pull-Through</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Platform maturity creates the conditions for ACM, ACS, ODF, and AMQ adoption.
            More products, more ARR.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:28px; margin-bottom:16px;">Enterprise Standardization</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            From one cluster to org-wide OpenShift standard.<br/>
            Multi-cluster means multi-year ARR.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        Growth becomes <span class="highlight">engineered</span> — not accidental.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Point to each lever. These map directly to ARR line items — keep it commercial.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Three specific things we move. First — workload acceleration. We get more production workloads running on OpenShift, which means more nodes, which means ARR grows as the platform scales. Second — portfolio pull-through. As we mature the platform, ODF, ACM, ACS, AMQ become natural next conversations. We create the conditions, not the pitch. Third — standardization. One cluster to many. That's multi-year, multi-site expansion. Growth stops being a conversation and starts being a process."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. Account Expansion Stories -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        What <span class="highlight">Account Expansion</span> Looks Like
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:28px;">

        <div style="background:white; padding:36px; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(26,13,50,0.08); position:relative;">
          <div style="height:4px; background:#FF5623; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; right:0; border-radius:16px 16px 0 0;"></div>
          <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:8px;">
            <img src="/logos/atg.png" alt="ATG" style="height:50px;">
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            <span class="highlight">Start:</span> OpenShift installed, adoption gap.<br/><br/>
            <span class="highlight">Outcome:</span> 7 years of sustained node growth. Platform became org-wide standard.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:white; padding:36px; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(26,13,50,0.08); position:relative;">
          <div style="height:4px; background:#FF5623; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; right:0; border-radius:16px 16px 0 0;"></div>
          <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:8px;">
            <img src="/logos/csn.png" alt="CSN" style="height:50px;">
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            <span class="highlight">Start:</span> Post-implementation gap. Nodes flat.<br/><br/>
            <span class="highlight">Outcome:</span> Node growth + ODF adoption. Expanded Red Hat portfolio footprint.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:white; padding:36px; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(26,13,50,0.08); position:relative;">
          <div style="height:4px; background:#FF5623; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; right:0; border-radius:16px 16px 0 0;"></div>
          <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:8px;">
            <img src="/logos/rs.png" alt="Region Skåne" style="height:50px;">
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            <span class="highlight">Start:</span> Single cluster, no expansion path.<br/><br/>
            <span class="highlight">Outcome:</span> Multi-cluster. New products. Org-wide OpenShift standard.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Walk through each card left to right. Reference the logos — they're real names.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Three accounts. Same starting point, same outcome. ATG started with OpenShift installed but not expanding. Seven years later — continuous node growth, org-wide platform. CSN — implementation gap, nodes flat. We stepped in. Nodes grew, ODF followed. Region Skåne — single cluster, no path forward. Now they're multi-cluster, new products, org-wide standard. The pattern is consistent because the problem is consistent."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 8. When to Engage -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        When to <span class="highlight">Bring Stakater In</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:50px;">

        <div style="padding:36px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">New Account</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Architect for expansion from day one. Don't wait for the plateau.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">6–12 Months Post-Implementation</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Nodes flat. Adoption slowing. Break the plateau before renewal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Before Renewal</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Strengthen the platform story. Introduce ODF, ACM, or ACS at the right moment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Expansion Conversation</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Multi-cluster, multi-product, multi-team. We co-design the platform growth strategy.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Invite the AE to map their own accounts to these triggers as you walk through each.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Four specific entry points. A brand new account — we can architect for expansion from day one, so you're not rebuilding momentum twelve months in. Six to twelve months post-implementation — that's the danger zone, nodes are flat, adoption is slowing. We break the plateau before renewal gets awkward. Before a renewal conversation — we help you walk in with a platform story, not just a price negotiation. And any time you're talking multi-cluster or portfolio expansion — we co-design that strategy with you."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 9. CTA -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>Let's Map Your Accounts.</h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Bring us three accounts with flat nodes.<br/>
        We'll show you where the ARR is.
      </h2>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h1 style="font-weight:800;">
        More Nodes. More Products. Stronger Renewals.
      </h1>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Keep the close tight. The offer is specific — make it easy to say yes.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Here's what I'd like to do. Pick three accounts from your book — ones with flat nodes, or coming up for renewal, or where adoption has stalled. We'll run them through our lifecycle model and map exactly where the ARR opportunity is. One conversation. No cost. You walk away knowing which accounts to prioritize and what the expansion play is for each. That's the starting point."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

</Deck>
